clomid i am thinking about taking clomid because i am not ovulating and have been ttc for months my ob said she would prescribe it to me do you think i should see an infertility doctor first or take clomid from my ob thanks many fertility doctors are ob's clomid is actually commonly prescribed to encourage ovulation i took clomid myself but it was unsuccessful for me i had other hormone issues that made the clomid ineffective however i have talked to many other women who have had success with it go ahead and take it from your ob otherwise if you go to a specialist some insurances may not cover the medication or procedures regarding fertility generally you need to have a referal that is pre approved by your insurance good luck Infertility In vitro fertilisation Menstrual cycle Fertility awareness Polycystic ovary syndrome Ovulation Pregnancy Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Transsexuality Emergency contraception Medicine Ovarian cyst Ovarian cancer Puberty Legal aspects of transsexualism Progesterone Obesity Childbirth Health insurance Gynaecology Medical prescription Endometriosis Bipolar disorder Insurance Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Terri Schiavo Oral contraceptive Osteopathy Pharmaceutical company Homeopathy Growth hormone treatment Urinary incontinence Psychiatry Stomach cancer Baldness treatments Androgen insensitivity syndrome Natural family planning Transgender Breastfeeding Estrus cycle Prolactinoma Alternative medicine Female genital cutting Abortion Physician Practices of Jehovah's Witnesses Nurse Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Lipoid congenital adrenal hyperplasia Pharmaceutical Benefits Scheme Medicare (Canada) General practitioner Sexual abstinence Stem cell Congenital adrenal hyperplasia Testosterone Ovary Dieting Gregory Goodwin Pincus Traditional Chinese medicine Fasting Turner syndrome National Health Service Publicly funded medicine Cryptorchidism Miscarriage Abortion in Canada Canadian and American health care systems compar